Re: て+いる　confusion
by tuber97 » Thu 11.11.2010 10:16 pm Dustin_Calgary wrote:Rather than to be "xx"ing, a motion verb with iru actually means "to have gone somewhere and still be there". So how would one write the progressive form of a motion verb? お前の魂をいただくよ。
