Re: て+いる　confusion
by Yudan Taiteki » Tue 11.16.2010 8:21 pm You can also just use a plain imperfective -- 家に帰る, which works in some cases.But in my discussions with native speakers about this, it just doesn't seem like there's any way to literally translate "I am going home [= I am on my way home]" in a way that is completely satisfactory to a native speaker.
-Chris Kern
Yudan Taiteki
